accountId.doc: Account ID of the experiment to update.

webPropertyId.doc: Web property ID of the experiment to update.

profileId.doc: Profile ID of the experiment to update.

experimentId.doc: Experiment ID of the experiment to update.

id.doc: Experiment ID. Required for patch and update. Disallowed for create.

name.doc: Experiment name. This field may not be changed for an experiment whose status is ENDED. This field is required when creating an experiment.

status.doc: Experiment status. Possible values: "DRAFT", "READY_TO_RUN", "RUNNING", "ENDED". Experiments can be created in the "DRAFT", "READY_TO_RUN" or "RUNNING" state. This field is required when creating an experiment.

variations.name.doc: The name of the variation. This field is required when creating an experiment. This field may not be changed for an experiment whose status is ENDED.

editableInGaUi.doc: If true, the end user will be able to edit the experiment via the Google Analytics user interface.

minimumExperimentLengthInDays.doc: Specifies the minimum length of the experiment. Can be changed for a running experiment. This field may not be changed for an experiments whose status is ENDED.

objectiveMetric.doc: The metric that the experiment is optimizing. Valid values: "ga:goal(n)Completions", "ga:bounces", "ga:pageviews", "ga:timeOnSite", "ga:transactions", "ga:transactionRevenue". This field is required if status is "RUNNING" and servingFramework is one of "REDIRECT" or "API".

optimizationType.doc: Whether the objectiveMetric should be minimized or maximized. Possible values: "MAXIMUM", "MINIMUM". Optional--defaults to "MAXIMUM". Cannot be specified without objectiveMetric. Cannot be modified when status is "RUNNING" or "ENDED".

rewriteVariationUrlsAsOriginal.doc: Boolean specifying whether variations URLS are rewritten to match those of the original. This field may not be changed for an experiments whose status is ENDED.

servingFramework.doc: The framework used to serve the experiment variations and evaluate the results. One of:REDIRECT: Google Analytics redirects traffic to different variation pages, reports the chosen variation and evaluates the results.API: Google Analytics chooses and reports the variation to serve and evaluates the results; the caller is responsible for serving the selected variation.EXTERNAL: The variations will be served externally and the chosen variation reported to Google Analytics. The caller is responsible for serving the selected variation and evaluating the results.

trafficCoverage.doc: A floating-point number between 0 and 1. Specifies the fraction of the traffic that participates in the experiment. Can be changed for a running experiment. This field may not be changed for an experiments whose status is ENDED.

variations.status.doc: Status of the variation. Possible values: "ACTIVE", "INACTIVE". INACTIVE variations are not served. This field may not be changed for an experiment whose status is ENDED.

variations.url.doc: The URL of the variation. This field may not be changed for an experiment whose status is RUNNING or ENDED.

winnerConfidenceLevel.doc: A floating-point number between 0 and 1. Specifies the necessary confidence level to choose a winner. This field may not be changed for an experiments whose status is ENDED.
